            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1711449390354-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly softened, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pan with 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[2 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[3 tsp] </span><strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>fresh tagliatelle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the tagliatelle for 3-4 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>tagliatelle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1711449393734-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
